To reverse the meaning of a noun, adjective or verb, you can add na, ni or n'
before the word. The rules are following:
  * Before a head noun ending in -am (or related adjective) use na, otherwise
    use ni. (in particular before a verb use ni)
  * If the word begins with a vowel, use n' instead of na and nij instead of ni.

Examples:
  garam   -   nagaram
  possna  -   nipossna
  arka    -   n'arka
  amna    -   nij'amna
  horem   -   nihorem
  ovem    -   nij'ovem

  geldem  -   nigeldem
  hik     -   nihik
  hladena -   nihladena
